FBIS4-34685 "drlat121_p_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 Ecuador Government Closes Several Radio Stations Government Closes Several Radio Stations PA2306042994 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 22 Jun 94 PA2306042994 Quito Voz de los Andes Spanish BFN [From "The Voz Andes Newscast"] [Text] [Name indistinct] has charged that the mobilization decree is unconstitutional and that military forces working in Cotopaxi, Tungurahua, Chimborazo, and El Loro have already silenced several radio stations and peasant groups. We reported during our noon newscast that Radio Latacunga in Latacunga had been closed, as well as the radio station of the Radio Schools in Chimborazo province. Manuel Mena, the General Communications Secretariat representative in Azogues, gave us the following report on the situation in the province. [Begin Mena recording] Answering your question, we have been strictly complying with the executive decree that went into effect at 2300 yesterday, in the province of [words indistinct]. General Ordonez, the Army commander of the [words indistinct] stationed in Cuenca, Azuay province, has issued the corresponding orders so that Army personnel can clear the roads in the sectors of [words indistinct] Canaro, Tambo, and onward, the [word indistinct] crossroad that divides the road leading to the coastal and northern areas of the country. Furthermore, you probably already know what is happening in the area where the residents have taken this long-lasting problem into their own hands [words indistinct]. The strike committee is presided over by Galo Penagil, the president of the municipal council in this area. They took this position of force and proceeded to close the roads that join the provinces of Guayas, Dos Rios, and El Loro in northern Ecuador. The situation is still very worrisome because, although it is true that the government decreed the state of emergency, the flow of traffic is still not normal [words indistinct] and shortages continue to be felt in the southern part of the country. [end recording]
